                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                                    Jose Brasa to join on Monday   New Delhi: Spanish coach Jose Brasa will join as India rsquo;s national hockey coach on Monday, according to IOA sources.   Brasa is arriving in Delhi late on Sunday night and will sign the contract the next day. He is expected to fly out to Kuantan, Malaysia a couple of days later to join the Indian team for the Asia Cup to be there from May 9 to 16.   Brasa, however, will not take over the reins of the Indian team in the Asia Cup and will leave it for coach in-charge Harendra Singh to handle the side independently throughout the tournament.  Yuki in last 4  New Delhi: Yuki Bhambri defeated Thai qualifier Peerakit Siributwong 6-3, 6-2 to move to the semi-finals of the $15,000 ITF Futures men rsquo;s event Thursday.  Yuki will now take on Weerapat Doakmaiklee who beat Ranjir Virali Murugesan. Sixth seed Vishnu Vardhan move to the semis outsmarting compatriot N. Sundar Prashant 7-6 (3), 6-0.  Bengal win 9-1  Margao: Bengal open their Under-21 Dutta Ray Trophy football championship campaign with a thumping 9-1 victory over Jammu and Kashmir.  Anjay Dey netted four goals including a hattrick while Avinaba Bag, Dipankar Das, Sukurnddin Laskar and Mithun Saha also scored.   
